## Stronger Alternative Citations

### For Design Pattern Claims
- Alexander, C. (1977). A Pattern Language. — The original pattern language
- Gamma et al. (1994). Design Patterns. — Gang of Four for software patterns
- Borchers (2001). A Pattern Approach to Interaction Design. — HCI patterns

### For Ethical Design
- Shilton, K. (2013). Values Levers: Building Ethics into Design. — Actual empirical work
- Wong, R. & Mulligan, D. (2019). Speculative Ethics at CHI. — Contemporary framing
- Gray, C. & Chivukula, S. (2019). Ethical Mediation in UX Practice. — Practitioner ethics

### For Visualization & Navigation
- Card, Mackinlay, Shneiderman (1999). Readings in Information Visualization.
- Bederson & Hollan (1994). Pad++. — Zoomable interfaces
- van Ham & Perer (2009). Search, Show Context, Expand on Demand.

### For AI Characters & Dialogue
- Cassell et al. (2000). Embodied Conversational Agents.
- Gratch et al. (2002). Creating Interactive Virtual Humans.
- Traum et al. (2008). Negotiation with Virtual Humans.

